@startuml c4-jotp-06-message-flow
title JOTP - Message Flow Sequence Diagram

participant "Sender\nProcess" as Sender
participant "Sender\nMailbox" as SenderMB
participant "Receiver\nMailbox" as ReceiverMB
participant "Receiver\nProcess Handler" as Receiver
participant "EventManager\n(optional)" as EventMgr
participant "Timer\n(optional)" as Timer

== Asynchronous Message Send ==

Sender ->> ReceiverMB: send(message)\n[non-blocking]
note over ReceiverMB
  Message queued to
  receiver's LinkedTransferQueue
  (lock-free MPMC)
end note
ReceiverMB -->> Sender: return void

note over Sender
  Sender continues immediately
  Does not wait for processing
end note

== Message Delivery & Processing ==

ReceiverMB ->> Receiver: dequeue message\nfrom mailbox
activate Receiver
Receiver ->> Receiver: match on message\ntype & pattern

alt StateMachine event
  Receiver ->> EventMgr: dispatch(event)\nto StateMachine
  activate EventMgr
  EventMgr ->> Receiver: handler(state, event, data)
  Receiver -->> EventMgr: new state
  deactivate EventMgr
else Regular message
  Receiver ->> Receiver: call handler\n(state, message)
end

Receiver -->> Receiver: nextState
note over Receiver
  Handler returns nextState
  State updated atomically
end note
deactivate Receiver

== Synchronous Request-Reply (ask with timeout) ==

note over Sender
  Sender wants reply
  Uses ask(message, timeout)
end note

Sender ->> SenderMB: create reply slot\n+ timeout
activate SenderMB
Sender ->> ReceiverMB: send(message)\nwith replyTo = sender's slot
activate ReceiverMB

ReceiverMB ->> Receiver: deliver message\nincluding replyTo
activate Receiver

Receiver ->> Receiver: process message\ncompute reply
Receiver ->> SenderMB: send reply\nto sender's slot
note over SenderMB
  Reply queued in sender's mailbox
end note
deactivate Receiver

SenderMB ->> Sender: dequeue reply\n(or timeout)
note over Sender
  Sender blocks on reply dequeue
  With timeout
  Returns Result<Reply, Timeout>
end note
deactivate SenderMB
deactivate ReceiverMB

== Timed Message Delivery ==

Sender ->> Timer: ProcTimer.send_after\n(delay, receiver, message)
activate Timer
Timer ->> Timer: schedule delivery\nvia ScheduledExecutor
deactivate Timer

note over Timer
  After delay expires
  Message automatically sent
  to receiver's mailbox
end note

Timer ->> ReceiverMB: send(message)\n[automatic]
activate ReceiverMB
note over ReceiverMB
  Timed message queued
  Same as regular send
end note
deactivate ReceiverMB

== Error Handling with Result ==

note over Sender
  Wrap message send in Result
  for error handling
end note

Sender ->> Sender: var result =\nResult.of(() -> send(...))
alt Success
  Sender -->> Sender: Success(unit)
else Failure
  Sender -->> Sender: Failure(exception)
end

@enduml
